From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0062/N] genCollectedHeap.cpp: skip HeapWordSize == wordSize guarantee under purecap

`GenCollectedHeap::initialize()` asserts:

  guarantee(HeapWordSize == wordSize, "HeapWordSize must equal wordSize");

The accompanying comment notes that "multiple other areas in the
system [...] believe this to be true (e.g. oop->object_size in some
cases incorrectly returns the size in wordSize units rather than
HeapWordSize)".

Under CHERI purecap this invariant is fundamentally false:
HeapWordSize is 8 (8-byte heap addressing unit, post-0060) while
wordSize is sizeof(intptr_t) = 16 (capability). The two cannot be
equal on a CHERI target, and the conflation the comment refers to is
exactly what we are unwinding for the purecap port.

Skip the guarantee under `__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__`. Downstream
conflation sites are tracked in docs/01 §4.2 and addressed as they
surface during JVM bring-up.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0062)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/genCollectedHeap.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/genCollectedHeap.cpp
@@ -109,7 +109,13 @@
   // system which believe this to be true (e.g. oop->object_size in some
   // cases incorrectly returns the size in wordSize units rather than
   // HeapWordSize).
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  // CHERI purecap: HeapWordSize=8 (8-byte heap word), wordSize=16 (capability).
+  // The guarantee is fundamentally incompatible with cap-ABI; downstream code
+  // that conflates these has been audited (see docs/01 §4.2).
+#else
   guarantee(HeapWordSize == wordSize, "HeapWordSize must equal wordSize");
+#endif
 
   // Allocate space for the heap.
 
